,"text":"(X: 72 = 500/7 ≈ 71 ug/día)","guid":"Y6_UOBJ7SRyuKOUApUlPmw","children":[]}]},{"id":"160","parent":"151","text":"Control en 6-8 semanas","guid":"tZ4wm6fUR-KSPgnCqqLOlQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"161","parent":"0","text":"Flujograma\\Ncompleto de\\Najuste","guid":"7m2xY0-gRhiC01gxBrMDlQ","children":[{"id":"162","parent":"161","text":"Control TSH 4-6 semanas tras cambio","guid":"3GxSRvanStSRpyZ-t7PtRA","children":[]},{"id":"163","parent":"161","text":"Si LOGRA objetivo","guid":"qkKfwVdeSUuqdgvb0AeqCg","children":[{"id":"164","parent":"163","text":"Control a los 6 meses","guid":"wzQ4yNCOQc6--nQuVLyadQ","children":[]},{"id":"165","parent":"163","text":"Luego CONTROL ANUAL","guid":"K_zJpQ6WTU2p8aNq9q6juw","children":[]}]},{"id":"166","parent":"161","text":"Si NO logra objetivo → ajustar terapia","guid":"LpwV70qUQv64_rHmNi0OAg","children":[]}]},{"id":"167","parent":"0","text":"Cuándo derivar a\\Nnivel SECUNDARIO","guid":"WNxBbDgJTcWZXLBKPIWoaw","children":[{"id":"168","parent":"167","text":"Persona mayor de 75 años","guid":"qgKHjoz7Q8u1aFIrC8G3sQ","children":[]},{"id":"169","parent":"167","text":"Embarazo (con o sin tratamiento)","guid":"oEiqSSmDTGm_GZmaD9n0YA","children":[]},{"id":"170","parent":"167","text":"Antecedente de cáncer tiroideo","guid":"oBaAVuZwQEC6DNqiXuH7NA","children":[]},{"id":"171","parent":"167","text":"Taquiarritmia o insuficiencia cardiaca","guid":"IUUfNsUETruBUxg8zRxKNA","children":[]},{"id":"172","parent":"167","text":"Sospecha hipotiroidismo CENTRAL","guid":"JBwtF__xR46A0ofoCeQJLw","children":[]},{"id":"173","parent":"167","text":"Mantención TSH elevada pese a tto adecuado","guid":"MHTS0veMT2mnxsmKez80bA","children":[]},{"id":"174","parent":"167","text":"Nódulo palpable","guid":"S4G24QVDQ6CJYcmEGuXflg","children":[]},{"id":"175","parent":"167","text":"Uso de fármacos\\Ndifíciles","guid":"8WfPn-NKTQiFkmZKllL9cg","children":[{"id":"176","parent":"175","text":"Amiodarona","guid":"d3TviOlzT42B1ZkhXO7Vbg","children":[]},{"id":"177","parent":"175","text":"Litio","guid":"cmNQrXAaR8G-N8sZBnQV-A","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"175","text":"Inhibidores tirosina quinasa","guid":"gDWzKBZFRQKnTv5IDs3Iqw","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"175","text":"Inmunoterapia inhibidores checkpoint","guid":"NJq0kdqOT-u3Hasz-vg6Kg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"180","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clínicas","guid":"Qc6dgr8HQpq2oTt2KrLTcQ","children":[{"id":"181","parent":"180","text":"Cada paciente tiene UNA TSH OBJETIVO propia","guid":"6GANQCOvSXmRbmYNf8Lf-g","children":[]},{"id":"182","parent":"180","text":"Antes de ajustar dosis → SIEMPRE revisar toma correcta (3 veces)","guid":"41nPE8rKT16b5PTbDCgpXA","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"180","text":"~50% falla por adherencia, no por dosis","guid":"il48JW0GSuOr5e62cSc9Uw","children":[]},{"id":"184","parent":"180","text":"Vida media 7 días → permite jugar con días de semana","guid":"4Nx8Ok-TSH-X8v4fHFWnyA","children":[]},{"id":"185","parent":"180","text":"En AM → \"a mayor edad, TSH objetivo más elevada\"","guid":"9eT6IaYIQX6uZQkhbwY-zA","children":[]},{"id":"186","parent":"180","text":"Sistema público solo tiene 100 ug → dividir por 7 para ajuste fino","guid":"FZGZhJZDTVebB7u97_Izzw","children":[]},{"id":"187","parent":"180","text":"Partir pastilla redonda solo a la mitad (en 4 se pierden microgramos)","guid":"O3uV6JLcTkCzCsdwMwFo1Q","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"180","text":"Preferir ajuste fines de semana (más fácil recordar)","guid":"KHecBZX1RCCSU2j2VTy_IA","children":[]},{"id":"189","parent":"180","text":"Mujer en edad fértil → TSH < 2.5 (preconcepcional SIEMPRE)","guid":"XTJIcvbDTLSIRWJ6BlgGFw","children":[]},{"id":"190","parent":"180","text":"Embarazo → ↑ requerimiento desde semana 4","guid":"F2Rdj_yRT_OPVEv3n-22CQ","children":[]},{"id":"191","parent":"180","text":"IBP crónicos son MUY frecuentes → sospechar si sube TSH","guid":"-Z3M2B4wTjaHVLyopTAvXQ","children":[]},{"id":"192","parent":"180","text":"TSH suprimida en AM → más fracturas, FA y eventos CV","guid":"ZeqEw2ChQhqJhgxpfotMgQ","children":[]},{"id":"193","parent":"180","text":"Si TSH persiste alta pese a dosis → descartar celíaca / EII","guid":"jYVPk8AHRW2gywkPfVVh-g","children":[]},{"id":"194","parent":"180","text":"Nunca suspender fármaco interferente → AJUSTAR LT4","guid":"aDsQUSq3RpuIo3zRTD-y4w","children":[]},{"id":"195","parent":"180","text":"Control TSH 6-8 semanas tras cualquier cambio","guid":"QEMGgyO2TVu7pihCbzUclg","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"180","text":"40% de pacientes crónicos están supra/subtratados","guid":"GyPNsN72RZG3ptmfwMHvmw","children":[]}]},{"id":"197","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"uUY-ZoTuTzWy_JRERhHKqg","children":[{"id":"198","parent":"197","text":"1. Jonklaas J, et al. Guidelines for the Treatment of Hypothyroidism. American Thyroid Association. Thyroid. 2014;24(12):1670-1751.","guid":"IsT2m4CKScezJYRgX34IEg","children":[]},{"id":"199","parent":"197","text":"2. MINSAL. Guía de Práctica Clínica Hipotiroidismo en personas de 15 años y más. Chile. 2023.","guid":"mfmPzuLjSiaLrEfkEd5L3Q","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"197","text":"3. Encuesta Nacional de Salud (ENS) Chile 2016-2017. MINSAL.","guid":"6SC3IOxTQ7qXur3X9dEiMA","children":[]},{"id":"201","parent":"197","text":"4. Chaker L, et al. Hypothyroidism. Lancet. 2017;390(10101):1550-1562.","guid":"3VctFzhRR4Kwb0XQa6cFTg","children":[]},{"id":"202","parent":"197","text":"5. Flynn RW, et al. Serum thyroid-stimulating hormone concentration and morbidity from cardiovascular disease and fractures in patients on long-term thyroxine therapy. J Clin Endocrinol Metab. 2010;95(1):186-193.","guid":"BxQHCifMQlyeJ4N0P0ZHig","children":[]},{"id":"203","parent":"197","text":"6. Sepúlveda MF. Tips para ajuste de levotiroxina. Curso Endocrinología y Diabetes GESUR. Hospital de Puerto Montt / Universidad San Sebastián. 2024.","guid":"_6KBIGqsS_ygAfFrbJG2wg","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":203,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Endocrinología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Endocrinología","filename":"Ajuste-Levotiroxina","id":"map_523","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"Ajuste-Levotiroxina"}